    /*
     * A client may send either a ClientHello or a HelloRequest. A server
     * must send a HelloRequest if it has not yet done so, and may do so
     * only if it has not received a HelloRequest from the client.  If the
     * client sends a HelloRequest, the server must treat it as a fatal
     * error if it has already sent a HelloRequest or if the client
     * has not sent a ClientHello message first.
